Title: 'So I Walked '
DateModified: '2018-02-11'
DatePublished: '2018-04-20'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2018/applications/so-i-walked
SetInCountry: Argentina
Category: Making a local connection
AuthorName: Jacob  Hill
AuthorCountry: United States of America
Text: A boy struggles with feeling alone in his small neighborhood outside Santa Fe,
  New Mexico.  His mothers is working three jobs, his father only alive in tanned
  photographs, he spends most of his evenings debating his purpose -- where he will
  go and where he has come from.  Yet, when he discovers his father way still be living
  in Bueno Aires, the boy packs his bags and catches a freight train across the border.  In
  a journey that test more than his spirit, the young boy sets out determined to find
  a long lost father; yet, in the process discovers a connection to his heritage the
  likes of which he couldn't have expected.  Written in a omniscient, memoir format,  "So
  I Walked" will follow a young man's journey into his past as he journeys South into
  adulthood.
